## Anti-Patterns (Avoid)

### ❌ WRONG: Server data in Zustand

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG - Don't store server data in Zustand
const useUserStore = create((set) => ({
  users: [],
  fetchUsers: async () => {
    const users = await api.getUsers();
    set({ users });
  },
}));

// ✅ CORRECT - Use TanStack Query
const { data: users } = useUsers();
```

### ❌ WRONG: Prop drilling

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<GrandParent user={user}>
  <Parent user={user}>
    <Child user={user} />
  </Parent>
</GrandParent>

// ✅ CORRECT - Zustand or Context
const user = useAuthStore((state) => state.user);
```

### ❌ WRONG: Duplicating state

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG - Duplicating server state
const { data: user } = useUser(id);
const [localUser, setLocalUser] = useState(user);

// ✅ CORRECT - Use server state directly
const { data: user } = useUser(id);
```

## Summary

| State Type | Tool | Use Case | Example |
|------------|------|----------|---------|
| **Server State** | TanStack Query | API data | Users, Orders, Products |
| **Client State** | Zustand | UI state | Sidebar open/closed, Theme, Auth |
| **URL State** | nuqs | Shareable state | Filters, Pagination, Search |
| **Form State** | React Hook Form | Form handling | Create/Edit forms |
